@startuml
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
title Nightfall - Deployment & Project Structure (Three.js + TypeScript)

cloud "Static Hosting (GitHub Pages / Cloudflare / Vercel)" as Host {
  folder "Vite Build Output" {
    artifact "index.html"
    artifact "assets/index-*.js"
    artifact "assets/index-*.css"
  }

  folder "WebLLM Nano Models" {
    artifact "phi-2-q4f16_1-webgpu.wasm"
    artifact "mlc-chat-config.json"
    artifact "params_shard_*.bin"
  }

  folder "Assets" {
    artifact "textures/"
    artifact "sounds/"
    artifact "models/"
  }
}

node "Client Browser" as Browser {
  component "Three.js Runtime" as ThreeRuntime
  component "WebLLM Runtime" as WebLLM
  component "WebGPU" as GPU
  database "IndexedDB" as Cache
  component "Rapier Physics (WASM)" as Rapier
}

actor "Human Player" as Player

' Flow
Player --> ThreeRuntime : "WASD + Mouse + Interaction"
ThreeRuntime --> WebLLM : "Query nano model for cat behavior"
WebLLM --> GPU : "Inference on nano models"
ThreeRuntime <--> Cache : "Load model weights & assets"
ThreeRuntime --> Rapier : "Physics simulation"

note right of ThreeRuntime
  Recommended TypeScript Project Tree:

  nightfall/
  ├── src/
  │   ├── main.ts
  │   ├── core/
  │   │   ├── Player.ts
  │   │   ├── HeartRate.ts
  │   │   ├── GameManager.ts
  │   │   └── Vision.ts
  │   ├── cats/
  │   │   ├── Cat.ts
  │   │   ├── CatBrain.ts
  │   │   └── behaviors/
  │   │       ├── StalkingBehavior.ts   ← Primary
  │   │       ├── FleeBehavior.ts
  │   │       └── MischiefBehavior.ts
  │   ├── environment/
  │   │   ├── Curtain.ts
  │   │   ├── House.ts
  │   │   └── lights/
  │   ├── interactables/
  │   │   ├── Interactable.ts
  │   │   ├── Note.ts
  │   │   └── Door.ts
  │   └── ui/
  │       ├── HUD.ts
  │       └── HeartMonitor.ts
  ├── package.json
  ├── tsconfig.json
  └── vite.config.ts
end note

note bottom of ThreeRuntime
  • Pure TypeScript + Three.js architecture
  • No heavy engine — small, modular classes
  • WebLLMConnector uses fetch / WebGPU directly
  • Reactivity via simple event emitters or signals
  • Easy to test and refactor with AI harness
end note

note right of WebLLM
  Nano models run completely in-browser.
  Each cat has a tiny rolling context.
end note

@enduml
